Check out the Darth Jar Jar Reveal Trailer for Fortnite, the hit third-person battle royale developed by Epic Games. Players will be able to play as the legendary and elusive Darth Jar Jar by unlocking the ability to purchase this outfit set by earning XP across any experience in Fortnite. Darth Jar Jar is available now for Fortnite.

#Fortnite #DarthJarJar #Gaming
title: Fortnite - Official Darth Jar Jar Reveal Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Check out the Kotaro Fuma Trailer for Onimusha 2: Samurai's Destiny, an upcoming remaster of the classic action game developed by Capcom. Players can become acquainted with Kotaro, a fearless warrior at the age of 17. Kotaro is a top-class ninja and is the young chief of the Fuma clan. Meet Kotaro in Onimusha 2: Samurai's Destiny, launching on May 23 for PlayStation 4 (PS4), Xbox One, Nintendo Switch, and PC (Steam).

#Onimusha2SamuraisDestiny #Gaming #IGN
title: Onimusha 2: Samurai's Destiny - Official Kotaro Fuma Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Star of Horizon Zero Dawn, Ashly Burch breaks down all her iconic characters from video games. From Aloy from Horizon Forbidden West to Mel in The Last of Us Part 2, Ashly Burch has played many incredible video game roles. 

Ashly Burch talks about her humble beginings in the YouTube series Hey Ash Whatcha Playin'? to her big break as the voice of Tiny Tina in Borderlands 2. Her career then progresses as she plays Chloe in Life is Strange, Kamala Khan in Lego Marvel Avengers and, most importantly, the voice of Aloy in Horizon Zero Dawn. 

More recently Ashly Burch stars in Mythic Quest, the Apple TV show created by Rob McElhenney. Ashly has also gone on the by the Executive producer of Side Quest, the Mythic Quest spin-off. Ashly Burch breaks down all these roles for us and explains everything she loves about all the iconic characters she's played.

00:00 -  Intro
00:37 - Tiny Tina, Borderlands 2
01:59 - Ashly Burch, Saints Row 4
03:06 - Chloe Price, Life is Strange
04:57 - Cassie Cag
title: Ashly Burch Breaks Down Her Iconic Characters - Horizon Zero Dawn, Borderlands, The Last of Us

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the Story Trailer for Persona 5: The Phantom X, an upcoming RPG in the world of Persona 5 developed by Atlus, SEGA, and Perfect World. Players will experience an all-new story with new characters that appeal to new fans of the franchise, alongside long-time fans of Persona 5. The protagonist sees a mysterious dream of a Velvet Room where a long-nosed man and a beautiful woman in blue reside... Persona 5: The Phantom X is launching on June 26 for iOS, Android, and PC (Steam).

#Persona5ThePhantomX #Gaming #IGN
title: Persona 5: The Phantom X - Official Story Trailer (Japanese VO)

author: IGN
description:
Take a look at The Weeknd Hub Collaboration Trailer for Roblox, the hit social creative-adventure game developed by Roblox Corporation. Players can now experience The Weeknd Hub, a place where fans can explore the lobby and the references to all of the Weeknd's eras within, as well as purchase an exclusive movie ticket + XO limited virtual chain bundle. Fans can also explore the Hurry Up Tomorrow map that drops fans into a key scene from the film before entering a hotel and battling "shadows" in a multi-player, single-player shooter game. The Weeknd Hub is available now in Roblox.

#Roblox #TheWeeknd #Gaming
title: Roblox x The Weeknd - Official Hub Collaboration Trailer
